{{Infobox ethnic group| |group=Afro-Bermudians |image= [[Image:Premier Paula Cox.jpg|81px]][[Image:Ewart Brown.JPG|89px]] |caption= [[Paula Cox]]{{*}} [[Ewart Brown]] |population= Approx. 37,000 |popplace= {{flag|Bermuda}} (Approx. 37,000<ref name=cia/>) |langs= [[Bermudian English]] |rels= [[Christianity]] |related= [[Afro-Caribbean]], [[Afro-Bahamian]] }}
'''Afro-Bermudians''' or '''Bermudians of African descent''', are [[Demographics of Bermuda|Bermudians]] whose ancestry lies within the continent of [[Africa]], most notably [[West Africa]].
Currently, Afro-Bermudians are the majority ethnic group in Bermuda, as they account for 53.8% of the country's population.<ref name=cia>{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/bd.html |title=CIA - The World Factbook -- Bermuda |accessdate=2013-03-16 |publisher=CIA | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100402000413/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/bd.html| archivedate= 13 February 2013 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref>
