{{Infobox criminal | name = Hassan Izz-Al-Din | image = Hasan Izz-Al-Din.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = Photograph of Hassan | birth_name = Hassan Izz-Al-Din | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1963}} | birth_place = [[Lebanon]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | residence = Unknown, thought to be hiding in Lebanon | nationality = [[Lebanese people|Lebanese]] | other_names = Ahmed Garbaya, Samir Salwwan, Sa-id | occupation = [[Terrorist]] | known_for = One of the FBI's Most Wanted Terrorists | height = 5'9-5'11 | weight = 145-150 lbs | predecessor = | successor = | religion = [[Islam]] | penalty = | conviction_status = | spouse = | children = | parents = <!--Do not include parents unless notable or they are relevant to the crime.--> | allegiance = [[Hezbollah|Lebanese Hizbollah]] | motive = [[Islamism]] | conviction = | reward_amount = [[USD]] $5,000,000 | capture_status = Fugitive | wanted_by = {{flagicon image|Flag of the United States.svg|25px}} [[United States]] | partners = | wanted_since = 1985 | time_at_large = | escaped = | escape_end = | comments = | victims = | date = | time = | beginyear = | endyear = | country = [[Lebanon]] | states = | locations = | targets = Civilians | fatalities = | injuries = | weapons = | apprehended = | imprisoned = | footnotes = }}
'''Hasan Izz-Al-Din''' ({{lang-ar|حسن عز الدين}}) (born about 1963) is a [[Lebanon|Lebanese]] national wanted by the [[United States]] government.
Hasan Izz-Al-Din is an alleged member of [[Hezbollah]]. He is currently wanted by the United States government for his alleged involvement in the June 14, 1985 [[Aircraft hijacking|hijacking]] of [[TWA Flight 847]]. This attack resulted in the death of [[United States Navy]] diver [[Robert Stethem]]. On October 10, 2001, Izz-Al-Din, along with two other alleged participants in the hijacking, was placed on the initial list of the FBI's top 22 [[FBI Most Wanted Terrorists|Most Wanted Terrorists]], which was released to the public by President [[George W. Bush]]. A reward of 5 million dollars is currently being offered for information leading to his arrest and conviction. It is believed he is residing in Lebanon.
