'''Jaswal''' is a [[Rajput]]<ref>Elliot's Hist, of India, VI, p. 129</ref> clan found in [[India]] and  Pakistan.

== Genealogy of Rajput clan ==
The Jaswal Rajputs are a branch of the [[Katoch]] clan of [[Kangra, Himachal Pradesh|Kangra]]. Their ancestor Raja Purab Chand was a brother of the Raja of Kangra, who carved out an independent kingdom in the Swaan valley, which came to be known as Jaswan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hpuna.gov.in/history.htm |title=State Government of Himachal Pradesh, India}}</ref>

The present head of the clan is Raja Naginder Singh, son of Raja Chain Singh Jaswal (since 1945) who lives in his ancestral palace at [[Amb, India|Amb]] ([[Una District]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hpuna.gov.in/history.htm |title=State Government of Himachal Pradesh, India}}</ref>

