The '''Zyoba''' are an ethnic and linguistic group based near [[Lake Tanganyika]] in [[Tanzania]] and the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] who speak the [[Joba language]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ethnologue.com/14/show_language.asp?code%3DZYO |title=Archived copy |accessdate=August 23, 2006 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070310214850/http://www.ethnologue.com/14/show_language.asp?code=ZYO |archivedate=March 10, 2007 }}</ref>

