{{Contains Khoekhoe text}} The '''ǀKhowesin''' (literally ''queen bees'', also: '''Witbooi Nama''' or '''Witbooi Orlam''') are one of five clans of the [[Orlam people]] in [[Namibia]]. They originated from [[Pella, Northern Cape|Pella]] in the [[Cape Colony]] in South Africa and migrated to South West Africa the 19th century, led by their [[tribal chief|Kaptein]] [[Kido Witbooi]]. They crossed [[Orange River]] and moved to the [[Fish River (Namibia)|Fish River]] area living a nomadic existence. They eventually settled in what became known later as [[Gibeon, Namibia|Gibeon]].{{sfn|Tonchi|Lindeke|Grotpeter|2012|p=212}}{{sfn|Dedering|1997|pp=59–61}}
